lead_paragraph: J.J. Redick had 23 points, including the tying 3-pointer late in regulation, and Jamal Crawford also scored 23 points to lead the short-handed Los Angeles Clippers to a 98-92 overtime victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Monday night.

headline.print_headline: Redick Leads Clippers to 98-92 OT Victory Over 76ers
